  "published": "2025-09-26",
  "runtimeMin": 141,
  "format": "Sean, Amanda, and Chris Ryan spoil 'One Battle After Another' in full. Then Sean sits down with Paul Thomas Anderson and Leonardo DiCaprio.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "'One Battle After Another'",
      "note": "Full spoilers · with Chris Ryan",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "One Battle After Another",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "PTA's 10th feature, loosely adapted from Thomas Pynchon's 'Vineland' but moved to the present day and shot on VistaVision. Leo plays Bob Ferguson, a burnt-out ex-revolutionary raising his daughter Willa (Chase Infinity) off-grid until his old nemesis Lockjaw (Sean Penn) resurfaces. A 40-minute prologue follows Perfidia Beverly Hills (Teyana Taylor) and the French 75, then jumps 16 years to a chase across California: the Bactan Cross siege, the rooftop skate escape, the Borrego Springs highway. The three panelists rate it the movie of the year and possibly the decade; Amanda calls it prescient, Chris says it lived up to impossible hype. Also with Regina Hall, Benicio del Toro as Sensei Sergio, and Johnny Greenwood's score."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Paul Thomas Anderson and Leonardo DiCaprio",
      "note": "The last great things they've seen",
      "guest": "Paul Thomas Anderson on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Vertigo",
          "year": 1958,
          "note": "PTA rewatched it as a reference for a film he's working on, after talking it through with Scorsese; it's also a VistaVision movie, and they shot a since-cut sequence in San Juan Bautista where Hitchcock filmed."
        },
        {
          "title": "Tom Horn",
          "year": 1980,
          "note": "Steve McQueen's second-to-last film, about the real Pinkerton detective, shot by John Alonzo. PTA had never seen it and calls it terrific."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
